<TITLE> Rony smashes ton against Pakistan Under-19s </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  Two unbeaten centuries from Pakistanis Ahmed Shehzad and Umar Amin overshadowed Rony Talukdar's ton at the close of the second day of the lone four-dayer at National Stadium Karachi Wednesday. The Pakistan Under-19 team posted 214 for one at stumps, still trailing by 129 runs after Bangladesh Under-19 team scored 343 all out in the first innings riding on Rony's 107 runs. Opener Shehzad (100) and one-down Umar (100) together blunted the Bangladeshi bowlers to put on 212 for the unbroken second wicket after pacer Rubel Hossain bowled opener Shah Masood (0) with scoreboard on two for one. Earlier, Bangladesh, having resumed the second day on 273 for seven, added another 70 runs losing remaining three wickets as Rony converted his overnight 52 to 107 off 141 balls that studded 11 fours and two sixes. b
